beer_description:
The WEST Hefeweizen is the 2011 SIBA Supreme Champion.
In the style of a Bavarian wheat beer, our Hefeweizen is an authentic blend of wheat and barley malt, hopped carefully and left naturally unfiltered with a clean aroma of banana and clove and a satisfying zing on the palette, topped with crisp, white foam.
Made by a supermarket chain. Have lowered alcohol from 5.2 to 5 to  4.8% to pay less tax. Gage Roads are only 25% owned by Woolworths Limited.
Hell
A big American style IPA with bucket loads of US hops. Lush tropical fruit flavours and deceptive drinkability given the higher abv.

This is the OG (original gangstah) of our Black Damnation series and the one that started it all. This beer is a blend of Struise Black Albert and De Molen Hel & Verdoemenis imperial stouts. Both beers on the very edge of darkness, of which the brewers' minds both sit on the verge of insanity.

Black Damnation is black as hell, filthy rich in the nose and boasts massive taste. This brew is the perfect marriage of the sweet, unxious flavors from Black Albert and the bitter charcoal and coffee profile from the Hel & Verdoemenis. Good luck finding some, the last batch was made in 2010!

Full bodied and robust, Goliath has real strength of character.

Traditionally craft-brewed with Pale & Crystal Malts for a sturdy ruby colour and rich malty taste. With a hefty wack of English Fuggles and Styrian Goldings hops for a classic refreshing bitterness. 

Slay your thirst! Hops English Fuggles and Styrian Goldings. Contains barely.

Warlock is a slightly spiced English Strong Brown Ale. Brewed  with pure maple syrup, honey, and a blend of sugars and spices. Together these ingredients give Winter Warlock a unique and subtle flavor to enhance its malty character.
Brewed in winter 2009 for Christmas 2010

A single hopped pale ale.

Originally the second beer in our series of occasional 'one hop' beers using more unusual hop varieties; but it was that good we had to brew it again.

Whilst originally cultivated in 2000 by the Golden Gate Roza Hop Ranch in Prosser, Washington (US) Apollo hops have only recently become more readily available. A pale amber, hoppy beer, made with hops with 18.7% alpha acids. This hop has strong citrus notes with the emphasis on orange; resiny and spicy. Enjoy!

The first spanish abbey beer.
Elaborada con malta de cebada de la comarca seg?n la tradici?n de los maestros cerveceros de Flandes, que Carlos V trajo consigo en su retiro a Yuste hace casi 500 a?os.
This traditional German ale is wheat-based and unfiltered, giving it a cloudy look.  It's medium bodied and has distinct flavors of banana and clove.

Dark, full-bodied, and rich in flavor, Green Man Porter is wonderfully easy to drink. It offers a creamy, smooth mouthfeel and finishes with distinctive chocolate notes. This traditionally crafted, award-winning British-style Porter, like a true rock star, enjoys a legendary following.

The Bush de No?l derives much of its rounded character from the use of roast caramel malts. The hops are carefully balanced with these, added in just the right proportions to develops its subtle hop aroma. There is also a robust fruity character, with the overall taste pleasingly consistent.

beer_description: A lustrous dark red London ale with a rich malt combination that lends complex notes of toasted caramel, raisins, chocolate, and roasted toffee. Very light hop additions let the true malt characters promenade throughout the duration of this pleasurable experience.

Our flagship Pre-Prohibition style lager is inspired by the all malt beers of the early 1900s. This full-bodied lager is smooth & well balanced. It delivers a crisp & refreshing taste. Medals: Bronze - Dublin Craft Beer Cup 2015
This award winning brown porter has roasted and caramel malt flavors balanced with a hoppy bitterness. Bronze medal winner 2010 World Beer Cup.

Desde 1853, o trabalho do nosso Mestre Cervejeiro ? transformar mat?ria-prima em obra-prima.
Sua primeira cria??o, Bohemia Pilsen, ? um absurdo de cerveja: leve, refrescante, com aroma frutado, malte 100% importado e l?pulo da Rep?blica Tcheca.
A cerveja Pilsen foi criada em 1842 na cidade de Pilzen, onde atualmente fica a Rep?blica Tcheca. Delicada, clara e com teor alco?lico m?dio, ? a mais consumida no mundo e tamb?m a preferida dos brasileiros.

Even before drinking it, you?re surprised by the explosion of fruity aromas from the dry-hopping with American hops. But the adventure only starts here. The combination of a Belgian Triple style body with a nice balanced IPA (Indian Pale Ale) bitterness takes you on a long trip of sensations.
American oak is seamed with flavour, which Innis & Gunn unlocks during a 37-day maturation that imparts a light vanilla-oak character to this delicious beer.
Brewed using traditional German ingredients and aged on American Oak. The beer itself is highlighted by Munich malt, Tettnang hops, and German Ale yeast, resulting in a clean, earthy flavor.
beer_name: Harpoon 100 Barrel Series #34: Oak Aged Dunkel

beer_description: House beer for Lillie's Q.

This holiday delight is an authentic ?Weihnachtsbock? (Christmas Bock) ? a really fantastic traditional German holiday beer style. Its deep amber color with just a hint of holiday crimson is derived from a select combination of premium European barley malts.

A keg-conditioned British style ale, available throughout the state.
Note: 22 oz. bottles contract-brewed by Sebago Brewing.

Minerva Imperial Tequila Ale, beer malt touches denoting well rounded. Incredible feeling of silk on the palate from its powerful 7% alcohol content. Aroma of fresh hops and faint hints of oak. Exquisite aftertaste of vanilla and snuff without leaving a soft, elegant touch of Tequila. Certainly this style of beer we are proud to be the first beer style 100% designed and engineered in Mexico.

EBC: 110
SRM: 55,9

Sa couleur ?b?ne et la puissance de son ar?me sont le r?sultat d?un subtil m?lange de malts sp?ciaux torr?fi?s. ? d?guster ? environ 8 ?C pour appr?cier la finesse de son go?t caram?lis?.

// The deep colour and powerful aroma of the Brown beer are the result of a subtle blend of special roasted malts. Ideally, it should be sampled at 8C in order to fully appreciate the sophistication of its caramelised taste. A mixture of caramel and chocolate malts bring out its dark colour and chocolaty flavour, hints of coffee and full-bodied nature. Its creamy, full head carries a fresh bitterness across the palette.

This seasonal favorite is a refreshing American Pale Ale brewed using large amounts of fresh Michigan Traverse City, Old Mission Hops! This Ale offers a wonderful refreshing flavor with a hint of pine notes accented with citrus. A once a year beer you can look forward to every harvest!

The Bush Ambr?e is flushed with a bitter-sweet taste, and a pleasing consistency, courtesy, in part, of its balanced caramel malts. Those malts also introduce a strong streak of roasted nuts, adding to this beer's stand out flavour. Despite its initial filtering, the re-fermentation has given the beer a natural cloudiness, while also making for a mild and tender mouth-feel.

beer_description: This full bodied beer was brewed with 80% Marris Otter malt, and a single variety of Domestic hops, in attempt to blend the English and American versions of the style.
Commissioned by John Martin of Belgium in 1912. The first variety of Guinness to be pasteurised, in 1930.

Rich in character with a deep mahogany color complete with a beautiful tan head. This traditional German style lager is malty-sweet, full bodied with notes of caramel to warm you up from the crisp winter air.
This beer?s velvety-smooth aroma introduces pleasant flavours of hops and wood. In the finish you will taste a subtle bitterness with smoky impressions and a hint of alcohol.
Red amber with English caramel malts and Cascade hops.

The name of this beer is "Peculiar Christmas" in English. This spiced Christmas ale is strange - and indeed a fusion beer. We have gathered inspiration from the Norwegian drink ?gl?gg?, and as such this is quite an uncompromising brew. Best served with ?goro? and ?fattigmann?. Recommended serving temperature 10?C/50?F, but you are free to try on higher temperatures...

Appearance
Pale yellow with a white head. The remaining beer yeasts give the beer a slight cloudiness.

Flavour
A full-bodied and pleasant finish. The subtle notes of coriander and orange peel give it a delicate, spicy aroma. The high fermentation process adds several more fleeting, fruity components.
Made with pear syrup. Used to be brewed by Brasserie Vervifontaine before going to Grain d'Orge.

Just as abbeys try to strengthen their communities by attracting new young monks, brewery Van Eecke introduced this blond Kapittel to answer the big demand for paler beers.

This 2010 Gold medal awarded blond Abbey-beer has a surprising smooth finish, is easy to drink with its 6.5 % alcohol volume.

Although some may call this beer a ?strong Belgian blond?, you?ll discover a lightly sour-sweet yeasty fruit on a par with mildly sweet pale malts and a refreshing flow of really fragrant, springy flower blossoms, orangey-citric fruity hops with a mildly mineral, chewy bitterness.

You know the expression, "A Velvet Glove and an Iron Fist"? It was coined to refer to a regime that used a soft exterior to hide its punishingly unforgiving nature. This seems an apt description for our Velvet Glove. Its placid appearance and unparalleled smoothness hide the truth; this is one fiendishly strong stout. Rich, chocolaty espresso dominates the flavor profile, with a velvety smooth texture that will haunt your senses.

Grab this no-fuss, balanced brew that?s ready to go anywhere. For your other hand? May we suggest a bottle opener. Munich and caramel malts make our flagship ale drinkable until the sun goes down. Or at least until all the ice in the cooler melts. Session responsibly.
A fruity and malty chestnut coloured ale. The warmth and flavour are derived from the crystal and chocolate malt combined with traditional English hops.

Dark Double Bock Lager. JosephsBrau Brewing Company's Winter Brew is a rich, dark bock, inspired by the beers Bavarian monks brewed to lift their spirits during the long fasts of Lent. Dark roasted Munich and caramel malts worked wonders for hungry monks. Our Winter Brew is sure to do the same for you.
Made with clover & wildflower honey, with a black raspberries added. Deep berry flavor and rich red color.

As deep and dark as the Moscow Nights and strong enough to warm the Czar's tootsies even in January! Based on an 1880 Whitbread Triple Stout recipe - the era when British brewers were in hot competition to sell strong beers to the countries of Northern Europe.
An award winning light and crisp derivative of German-style K?lsch bier with a hint of sweetness. This quenching ale is a perfect outdoor companion!

White Lager Brewed With Spices.
Shmaltz Brewing Company reveals a most charming attraction: the sensual dance of provocative hops and spices entwined with a sumptuous and elegant malt body. Taste the rapture. Surrender to temptation. Seduce and be seduced.

Vagabond is the second offering in our limited 375 ml series. With only 500 bottles made, this beer is from one of the only barrels to move with us into our new brewery three years ago. Aged four years in American oak barrels, it boasts a complex aroma of maple syrup and port, with background notes of marzipan, plum and dill. Flavors of tart, unripened plum and caramel give way to a warming, toasted almond finish.
Beware, drinker! Hop hysteria could happen to you! Especially after indulging in our dry-hopped Double IPA's shockingly intense tropical aromas and hair-raising bitterness.

The biggest Marble in the pack, this dark golden India pale ale is ?Pint? grown up, we are proud of its pronounced New Zealand hop character and smooth biscuit base offset by fruit aroma. This beer just keeps on giving.

beer_description: THAT?S IT! We?re throwing down the gauntlet. Literally. If you haven?t tried craft brewed beer before, put the bottle you?re current-ly holding down and start somewhere else. This is not a good place to start. The Gauntlet is one seriously intense beer that should be reserved for only the boldest beer revolutionaries in the world. The inordinate amount of hop flavor and aroma that radiates from this creamy, froth covered liquid is enough to make this Brewmaster blush. If that sounds good to you, you can safely break your time on this earth down into 2 categories; the time before you tried The Gauntlet, and the time after. If not, the $5.00 50 packs are on the left

It?s that season again, time for giving thanks, eating lots, and pumpkin beer! We made this batch of pumpkin ale with about 75 pounds of pumpkins that we chopped up and roasted ourselves, in addition to pumpkin pie spice to add to the aroma and flavor. This beer has a medium body and a low hopping to let the pumpkins to shine through.
An American-Style India Pale Ale brewed with plenty of body and an assertive hop profile. Hops: Simcoe, Centennial, Amarillo. Malts: Premium Two Row, Munich, Crystal. 6.1 ABV. 94 IBU
This cider is light in body and features mouthwatering raspberry notes. It retains a dry and sparkling finish.
This full bodied copper coloured beer displays a delicate blend of cloves, coriander and heaps of fiery ginger.

Known as Monk?s Brew in the U.S.

Monk?s Elixir is a heavy dark Belgian ale inspired by the Trappist monasteries of Rochefort and Westvleteren. The beer style, characterized by its high content of alcohol, distinguishes itself by its dominant yeast character, delicious malt background and balanced hop notes.
2008 winner created by Samuel Adams employee Carissa Sweigart.

Twilight of the Idols is our Winter Porter. We brew Twilight each Autumn, with a touch of coffee, and age it on a blend of select vanilla beans. Originally conceived with a friend in 2009 while brewing in Denmark, the name of the annual release is inspired by the title of the last text written by one of our philosophical idols, Fredrich Nietzsche.

beer_description: If you dream of wheat this brew will get your toes tapping. Since 1995 we have brewed Bavarian style wheat beers exclusively for the same great state that grows and malts our own Wisconsin wheat. In a world full of posers this a true hefe-weizen naturally 100% bottle fermented and hazy. Expect this beer to cascade effervescent into your glass. The rich spicy clove and cinnamon notes will greet your nose while sweet fruit and wheat kiss your lips. Lick the foam from your mouth and admit sometimes you just gotta get up and dance.

An India pale ale with a golden malt base complimenting a quadruple addition of hops. All of which precede a floral and bitter finish. A proud contemporary classic, just like its name sake the 1927 Lagonda.

beer_description: Burnished gold hue with a persistent, rocky white head. Floral, spicy aroma redolent of lilacs, white pepper, and Barlett pears with undertones of blueberry honey and roses. A pleasant balance of crisp hop bitterness and clean malts adorn the spicy, herbal hop flavors lasting into a dry, refreshing finish.

The much awaited release of Pisgah's Vortex series has begun. The first offering is a triple Pale Ale weighing in @ 10.8% and 133 IBU. This beer is packed with Chinook and Nugget hops throughout the boil. The refined bitterness within is the trademark our use of whole hop flowers and the aroma is due to 1# of dry hops per barrel for a number of loving weeks. Treat youself with caution!

Xingu is a dark, select and refined beer, with a medium body and creamy foam. A 100% Brazilian product uses ingredients of the highest quality, it has a presence throughout Brazil.

Due to its balanced and authentic flavor, Xingu was recognized internationally by the Beverage Institute Tasting of Chicago as the best dark beer in the world, and for its quality by the International Taste & Quality Institute of Belgium in 2006.

The success of Xingu is not limited to Brazil, as it is present in the United States and Europe in its Long Neck version.
The flavour of this beer is pleasantly soft and is characterized by a delicate bitterness where the balance between malt and hop is based upon a fruity orange taste with a straight fresh after taste.

The Lonely Blonde wears a delicate fragrance of German noble hops, and slips a touch of white wheat between American pale and crystal malts for a smooth, sensuous body, fair complexion, and a pleasantly lacy white head. Crisp carbonation slinks the Lonely Blonde quickly away, and you?re left with nothing but a slight lingering sweetness.

Michigan pears fuel a second fermentation, providing subtle nuance
between grain & fruit. A slumber on oak and local raspberries adds depth and tartness.
